import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('state')['zip_code'].count().reset_index()
    sns.barplot(x='state', y='zip_code', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of zip codes across states?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.countplot(x="county", data=data, order=data['county'].value_counts().index)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    chart.set(xlabel='County', ylabel='Number of Zip Codes')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of zip codes across counties?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

    city_counts = data['city'].value_counts()
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.barplot(x=city_counts.index, y=city_counts.values, palette='Blues_d')
    plt.title('What is the most common city name in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.xlabel('City')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Zip Codes')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
